videos.description: Seminoles' quarterback James Blackman is rocked by the Tigers' Tre Lamar who forces and recovers the fumble.
videos.headline: Clemson's Lamar forces and recovers fumble

videos.description: In the final play of the 1st quarter, Tigers' Austin Bryant sacks Seminoles' quarterback James Blackman.
videos.headline: Clemson ends first quarter with sack

videos.description: Brian Burns forces Tavien Feaster to fumble in the red zone giving Florida State the ball deep in their own territory.
videos.headline: Florida State defense prevents TD with forced fumble

videos.description: On the first play of the drive, Travis Etienne rips off a powerful 28-yard run to add to Clemson's lead.
videos.headline: Clemson scores on 28-yard run from Etienne

videos.description: Apparently three Seminoles isn't enough to recover a fumble as Kelly Bryant out hustles them to secure the loose ball.
videos.headline: How many Seminoles does it take to recover a fumble?

videos.description: Dabo Swinney says he likes what he's seen from his defensive front so far, but the offense can't turn the ball over in the second half.
videos.headline: Swinney wants to see a cleaner second half

videos.description: On the punt, Emmett Rice hits Ryan Carter and taunts him after the play. Rice was ejected and Carter is being looked at by the trainers.
videos.headline: Florida State's Rice ejected for targeting

videos.description: James Blackman fires a 38-yard pass to Nyqwan Murray to move the Seminoles in to scoring position.
videos.headline: Blackman connects with Murray to set up score

videos.description: Jacques Patrick runs it in from the 3-yard line to cut Clemson's lead late in the third quarter.
videos.headline: Florida State gets on the board with short TD

videos.description: Nyqwan Murray fails to maintain control therefore the pass is incomplete and Murray is shocked.
videos.headline: FSU's Murray in disbelief he didn't make a big catch

videos.description: James Blackman finds Ryan Izzo wide open and he runs the rest of the way for the 60-yard score to make it a three point game.
videos.headline: FSU creates close game with 60-yard TD

videos.description: Kelly Bryant keeps the ball but then he fumbles it and the Seminoles recover giving them possession as they trail by 3.
videos.headline: Bryant fumbles and FSU recovers it

videos.description: After Clemson's offense turned the ball over, Van Smith intercepts James Blackman's pass to give the Tigers the ball back.
videos.headline: Clemson defense answers on the next play with a turnover

videos.description: Travis Etienne runs it in from the 1-yard line to make it a two possession game late in the fourth quarter.
videos.headline: Clemson scores from 1-yard line to extend lead

videos.description: Adam Choice finds his way into the end zone for a 10-yard score to add to Clemson's lead.
videos.headline: Clemson adds 10-yard TD with under a minute to go

videos.description: Clemson head coach Dabo Swinney says his defense played a heck of a game and he is happy that his team has found a way to keep winning week after week.
videos.headline: Dabo proud of his defense stepping up to beat FSU
